orm\" data-badge=\"inline\" data-size=\"invisible\"><\/div><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-field-group elementor-column elementor-field-type-submit elementor-col-100 e-form__buttons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<button class=\"elementor-button elementor-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-1408efa elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"1408efa\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-9e89438\" data-id=\"9e89438\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-dc10368 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"dc10368\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Types of ants in Canada<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-fba6bbf elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"fba6bbf\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>There are many different types of ants in Canada, and many of them are known for causing problems in homes. Some of Canada&#8217;s most common ant species include the black carpenter, pavement, pharaoh, odorous house, Argentine, and thief ant. Each of these ants can cause structural damage to homes, and black carpenter ants are the most common to cause this type of damage.<\/p><p>Ants can be a difficult problem to manage and control. It is important to know what species of ant you are dealing with before trying to remove them. Knowing basic information on the appearance, behavior, nesting habits, and type of problems ants cause can help identify the ant species to use proper control methods<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-67d27b4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"67d27b4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Appearance and Identification<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ad1babe elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ad1babe\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Ants are easily identifiable by their black, dark brown, red, or tan color, size (1.5 mm to 13 mm in length), and constricted petioles on their thorax and abdomen. They also have three pairs of legs for walking. They don&#8217;t have wings, but some ants, such as the reproductive Swarmers, have two pairs of functional wings.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0fda65f elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"0fda65f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Habitat<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f5b49f1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"f5b49f1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Habitat is a vital component of the lives of ants. Without a habitat, ants would not be able to survive. Ants live in colonies; each colony typically has a specific area in which it lives. The three castes of ants in a colony are the queen, drones, and workers. The queen is the only one who can lay eggs and controls most aspects of the colony. The workers forage for food and bring it back to the colony. Foraging often gets ants into the home because they are attracted to nearly any food humans may leave out. Ants are particularly attracted to sugary foods, meat, and grease.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1c8ee5c elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"1c8ee5c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Food<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a3b471c elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"a3b471c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Most ants in Canada feed on a combination of plant-based and protein-rich foods. Some of the familiar food sources for ants in Canada include:<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e402263 elementor-tabs-view-horizontal elementor-widget elementor-widget-tabs\" data-id=\"e402263\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"tabs.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tabs\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tabs-wrapper\" role=\"tablist\" >\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-title-2391\" class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-desktop-title\" aria-selected=\"true\" data-tab=\"1\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2391\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Insects<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-title-2392\" class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-desktop-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"2\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2392\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Honeydew<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-title-2393\" class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-desktop-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2393\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Nectar<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-title-2394\" class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-desktop-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"4\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2394\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Seeds<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-title-2395\" class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-desktop-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"5\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2395\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Fungi<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-title-2396\" class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-desktop-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"6\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2396\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Dead animals<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tabs-content-wrapper\" role=\"tablist\" aria-orientation=\"vertical\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title\" aria-selected=\"true\" data-tab=\"1\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2391\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Insects<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-2391\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"1\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-2391\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"false\"><p>Many species of ants are predatory and feed on other insects, such as flies, spiders, and caterpillars.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"2\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2392\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Honeydew<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-2392\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"2\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-2392\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p>Some species of ants feed on the sugary secretions of aphids and other sap-sucking insects, known as honeydew.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2393\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Nectar<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-2393\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-2393\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p>Certain species of ants feed on the nectar produced by flowers.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"4\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2394\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Seeds<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-2394\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"4\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-2394\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p>Some ants are seed predators and feed on the seeds of plants.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"5\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2395\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Fungi<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-2395\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"5\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-2395\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p>Some ants cultivate fungi as a food source by creating underground gardens where they grow and consume fungi.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"6\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2396\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Dead animals<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-2396\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"6\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-2396\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Some ants are scavengers and feed on the carcasses of dead animals.<\/span><\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-5aff669 elementor-reverse-mobile elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"5aff669\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-e22055b\" data-id=\"e22055b\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c8ede15 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"c8ede15\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Lifecycle<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-53f30e0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"53f30e0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Ants are one of the fascinating insects in the world. Let&#8217;s take a closer look at the lifecycle of ants in Canada.<\/p><p><strong>Egg Stage<\/strong><br \/>The lifecycle of ants begins with the egg stage. Queen ants lay eggs that hatch into larvae. The eggs are small and white, and they are laid in clusters.<\/p><p><strong>Larvae Stage<\/strong><br \/>Once the eggs hatch, the larvae emerge. Larvae are small, legless, and grub-like. They do not have eyes or antennae and cannot move around independently. During this stage, the larvae are fed by worker ants, who regurgitate food for them. The larvae molt several times, shedding their skin as they grow.<\/p><p><strong>Pupa Stage<\/strong><br \/>After the larvae have grown to a specific size, they enter the pupa stage. The pupae are enclosed in a cocoon during this stage and undergo metamorphosis. The pupae resemble adult ants, but they are still developing and not fully formed.<\/p><p><strong>Adult Stage<\/strong><br \/>Finally, the pupae emerge from their cocoons as fully formed adult ants. Adult ants may be workers, soldiers, or reproductive individuals, depending on the species. Workers are sterile females who perform various tasks within the colony, such as caring for the young, foraging for food, and defending the nest. Soldiers are also sterile females, but they are larger and have specialized mandibles for defense. Reproductive individuals include queens and males. Queens are the largest ants in the colony and are responsible for laying eggs. Males are smaller and their sole purpose is to mate with the queen.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-592fbc8\" data-id=\"592fbc8\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-56f11ec elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"56f11ec\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Ant-life-Cycle.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-image-5770\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Ant-life-Cycle.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Ant-life-Cycle-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Ant-life-Cycle-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Ant-life-Cycle-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Ant-life-Cycle-768x768.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-dd6ac17 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"dd6ac17\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-d99862a\" data-id=\"d99862a\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0b5f6c1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"0b5f6c1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Can ants bite?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-50a6cb0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"50a6cb0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Ants are tiny insects that are commonly found in various parts of the world, including Canada. Despite their small size, ants have developed remarkable adaptations to help them survive in their habitats. One of the adaptations that ants have developed is their mouthparts, which are specialized for biting and chewing solid food. This has led many people to wonder whether ants bite and how dangerous their bites can be.<\/span><\/p><p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">The answer is that some species of ants can indeed bite, but the severity of the bite depends on the species. The jaws of some ants are strong enough to bite through human skin, but not all. In Canada, for example, the majority of ant species rarely inflict bites on humans.<\/span><\/p><p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">However, some species of ants can bite and even inject venom into the wound. One example is the black carpenter ant, which can bite if provoked. The bite of a black carpenter ant can be painful and may cause a local reaction, but it is generally not dangerous to humans.<\/span><\/p><p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Another species of ant that is known to bite and the sting is the European Fire ant. This species injects formic acid into the wound, which can cause a burning sensation at the site of the bite. While the sting of a European Fire ant is not typically life-threatening, it can be pretty painful and uncomfortable.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-53374e1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"53374e1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Ants with wings<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b5dcb76 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b5dcb76\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">The hierarchical social structure of ants with wings is one of the fascinating aspects of this insect. Winged ants, also called alates, are a unique group of ants that undergo a nuptial flight to mate with a queen. After mating, the queens detach their wings and lay eggs. Winged males, on the other hand, die after completing the nuptial flight.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-97d3a2e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"97d3a2e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Habitat<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-78f000b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"78f000b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Habitat is a vital component of the lives of ants. Without a habitat, ants would not be able to survive. Ants live in colonies; each colony typically has a specific area in which it lives. The three castes of ants in a colony are the queen, drones, and workers. The queen is the only one who can lay eggs and controls most aspects of the colony. The workers forage for food and bring it back to the colony. Foraging often gets ants into the home because they are attracted to nearly any food humans may leave out. Ants are particularly attracted to sugary foods, meat, and grease.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6c154f0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"6c154f0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Problems caused by ants<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2ca2047 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2ca2047\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Ants can be a nuisance when found inside a home, and some species, like pharaoh ants, have been implicated in disease transmission. Also, ants can cause damage to lawns, gardens, and electrical cables when nesting indoors. A reaction to ant venom may result in sting site swelling, cramps, and headaches for some individuals.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-6cead1f elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"6cead1f\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-9807745\" data-id=\"9807745\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5be1615 elementor-view-default elementor-position-top elementor-mobile-position-top elementor-widget elementor-widget-icon-box\" data-id=\"5be1615\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"icon-box.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-icon-box-wrapper\">\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-icon-box-icon\">\n\t\t\t\t<span  class=\"elementor-icon elementor-animation-\">\n\t\t\t\t<i aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"far fa-flag\"><\/i>\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-icon-box-content\">\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-icon-box-title\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span  >\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tOur Guarantee\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h3>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"elementor-icon-box-description\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\tAcme Pest Solutions is dedicated to providing exceptional pest control services focusing on customer satisfaction. We aim to exceed industry standards by delivering high-quality work. We stand behind our work with a guarantee for each job completed, giving customers peace of mind. We are committed to ensuring seamless and high-quality service and will return to make things right if any issues arise.\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-0c82830 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"0c82830\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-3db8011\" data-id=\"3db8011\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-cbc6d5f elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"cbc6d5f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Ant Infestation: How to Deal with Ants in Your Home<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-df5c7e5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"df5c7e5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Ants are a common pest in many households, particularly in Canada. These tiny creatures are often attracted to the food and water sources found inside homes, making it challenging to keep them out. If you&#8217;re dealing with an ant infestation in your home, it&#8217;s important to act quickly to prevent the problem from getting worse. We&#8217;ll look at some effective ways to deal with ants in your home.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ded0c79 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"ded0c79\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Identify the Type of Ants<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f981dbf elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"f981dbf\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">The hierarchical social structure of ants with wings is one of the fascinating aspects of this insect. Winged ants, also called alates, are a unique group of ants that undergo a nuptial flight to mate with a queen. After mating, the queens detach their wings and lay eggs. Winged males, on the other hand, die after completing the nuptial flight.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6b120c9 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"6b120c9\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Eliminate Food Sources<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e2ddb0e elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e2ddb0e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Ants are attracted to food, so the first step in controlling an infestation is to eliminate their food sources. Keep your kitchen clean and free of crumbs, spills, and other food debris. Store food in airtight containers, and don&#8217;t leave pet food out for extended periods. Clean up spills and crumbs immediately, and don&#8217;t leave dirty dishes in the sink.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e6b04ad elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"e6b04ad\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Seal Entry Points<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c62f618 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c62f618\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Ants can enter your home through even the tiniest cracks and openings. Seal any gaps or holes in your walls, floors, and foundation to prevent ants from getting in. Check your windows and doors for gaps, and use weatherstripping to seal them up. Seal gaps around pipes and wires with caulk or foam insulation.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e4e3bb5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"e4e3bb5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Call a Professional<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-57bfff4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"57bfff4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">If you&#8217;ve tried all the above methods and are still dealing with an ant infestation, it may be time to call a professional pest control company ACME Pest Solutions. We have access to stronger, more effective insecticides that can eliminate the problem quickly and safely. A professional can also help identify the source of the infestation and provide tips on preventing future problems.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Ants Identification Size Color Description Size The average ant measures about 10 to 70 millimeters across the thorax or chest area. Color Black, dark brown, red, or tan Description Ants are divided into three parts: head, thorax and abdomen. The thorax is joined to the abdomen by nodes. A reproductive ant has wings, but every &#8230; <a title=\"Ant\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/ant\/\" aria-label=\"More on Ant\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":5710,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[37],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-5708","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-pest-libraries"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/5708"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=5708"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/5708\/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/5710"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=5708"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=5708"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=5708"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}